"{\"uid\": \"foxnews.com-live-news-olympics-2024-paris-august-6\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 75, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92026 FOX News Network, LLC.\", \"from\": 76, \"to\": 104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 82, \"end\": 98, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"FOX News Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quotes displayed in real-time or delayed by at least 15 minutes.\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Market data provided byFactset.\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Powered and implemented byFactSet Digital Solutions.Legal Statement.\", \"from\": 223, \"to\": 291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mutual Fund and ETF data provided byRefinitiv Lipper.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 308, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.620349693369804e-26, \"text\": \"ETF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics continues on Tuesday, August 6th.\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Equestrian, diving, sailing, skateboarding, wrestling, athletics and cycling will be among the sports to have gold medal events.\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Covered by:Ryan Gaydos,Paulina DedajandJackson Thompson  Coverage for this event has ended.\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 541, \"end\": 545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.9832347859414042, \"rank\": 0.017050542949947695, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}, {\"begin\": 577, \"end\": 585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.976923182653772, \"rank\": 0.02362193198291886, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA ended day 12 of the Paris Olympics in sole possession of most gold medals for the first time in the medal table since the games began.\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. finished off Tuesday with 24 golds, surpassing China with 22.\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 826, \"end\": 831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.8850275997208287, \"rank\": 0.12649552427268743, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China has led in total golds for most of the Olympics prior to Tuesday.\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 841, \"end\": 846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.8850275997208287, \"rank\": 0.12649552427268743, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. also leads in total silvers with 31 and total bronzes with 31, with a leading medal total of 86 - 27 more than China for second place.\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 1057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1034, \"end\": 1039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.8850275997208287, \"rank\": 0.12649552427268743, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tuesday's surge to the top was highlighted by 22-year-old surfing sensationCaroline Markswinning gold in the women's final in Tahiti and American sprinterGabby Thomaswinning gold in the women's 200-meter final.\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1185, \"end\": 1191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9987472973646001, \"rank\": 0.0012541442192977902, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1196, \"end\": 1204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9928569941647786, \"rank\": 0.0067983124608375165, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. women's water polo team advanced to the semifinal round as it looks to claim its fourth straight Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The team defeated Hungary 5-4 on Tuesday, and will now advance to the semifinal against Australia on Thursday.\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1487, \"end\": 1496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9995453400767572, \"rank\": 0.00028726468377498484, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Goal keeper Ashleigh Johnson saved 17 shots -a tournament-high - stopping 81% of Hungary's attempts.\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1523, \"end\": 1539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Johnson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ashleigh Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Johnson\"}, {\"begin\": 1592, \"end\": 1599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9976604843862971, \"rank\": 0.0022781377149891013, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Rachel Fattal scored the goal to put the Americans over one point at the end of the game.\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1623, \"end\": 1636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Fattal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rachel Fattal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Fattal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Fattal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBA veteranKevin Durantclimbed to the top of U.S. basketball historic leaderboard on Tuesday, breaking the record for most points scored by an American player.\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1873, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1714, \"end\": 1717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999998184421, \"rank\": 1.6734027833400755e-10, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1857, \"end\": 1865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9928569941647786, \"rank\": 0.0067983124608375165, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Durant passed women's star\\u00a0Lisa Leslie for the mark during theU.S.\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1902, \"end\": 1913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Leslie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lisa Leslie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Leslie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Leslie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'s 122-87 quarterfinalvictory against Brazil on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 1997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1979, \"end\": 1985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9575822599715312, \"rank\": 0.044292490322798805, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Durant's basket with 3:06 left in the third quarter gave him six points in the game and 489 in his four Olympic appearances.\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Leslie finished her four Olympic appearances with 488 points and four gold medals.\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2124, \"end\": 2130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Leslie\", \"score\": 0.9999982220773407, \"rank\": 8.771105079650861e-07, \"text\": \"Leslie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Leslie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Leslie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Durant had11 points in the game, so the new record is 494 - and counting.\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Durant is bidding to become the first men's player in Olympic history with four golds after being part of the U.S. teams that won titles at London 2012, Rio de Janeiro 2016 and the Tokyo Games that were held three years ago.\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2506, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He's one of only five U.S. players with at least 300 points in Olympic competition, joining Leslie, WNBA career scoring leader Diana Taurasi (416 entering the U.S. women's quarterfinal game Wednesday), the retired Carmelo Anthony (336) and James, who is presumably playing in the Olympics for the final time and entered Tuesday with 316 points in his four appearances.\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2635, \"end\": 2648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Diana Taurasi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Durant is also the U.S. career men's leader in rebounds in Olympic play, entering Tuesday with 126.\", \"from\": 2878, \"to\": 2977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He secured that record in the group-stage finale Saturday against Puerto Rico, his four rebounds in that game allowing him to pass both Anthony (125) and David Robinson (124) for the top spot there.\", \"from\": 2978, \"to\": 3176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3044, \"end\": 3055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Rico_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.6219091888702959, \"rank\": 0.5796727003807258, \"text\": \"Puerto Rico\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Rico_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Rico_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3132, \"end\": 3146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Robinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.4599156101546035e-16, \"text\": \"David Robinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Robinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Robinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Associated Press contributed to this report  The U.S. men's basketball team blew past brazil in the quarterfinal 122-87 on Tuesday but veteran superstar LeBron James had to come out of the game after taking an elbow to the face.\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3410, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3182, \"end\": 3198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/AP_Poll\", \"score\": 0.8982590520053654, \"rank\": 0.11326458469881627, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/AP_Poll\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/AP_Poll\"}, {\"begin\": 3231, \"end\": 3235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9506111405759857, \"rank\": 0.05193019376305404, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3335, \"end\": 3347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"James was seen with a wound near his left eye after the hit from Brazil's Georginho de Paula in the third quarter.\", \"from\": 